The White House will be hosting a Juneteenth Concert on Tuesday, June 13. This concert aims to celebrate community, culture, and music. In 2021, President Biden signed legislation to establish Juneteenth as a Federal holiday, emphasizing the importance of this day in American history. The concert will also coincide with Black Music Month, highlighting American art forms that reflect the soul of the American experience. The event is supported by organizations such as the National Endowment for the Arts, National Endowment for the Humanities, Pernod Ricard USA, STARZ #TaketheLead Initiative, and The Recording Academy.